The paper deals with the problem of computing data placement strategies in a distributed setting, which is a core problem in distributed databases and distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses graph partitioning algorithms to solve the data placement problem, which falls under the scope of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses load balancing, replication, and materialized views, which are common topics in distributed systems and may fall under cs.Distributed (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
